
Overview of noun castration

The noun castration has 3 senses (no senses from tagged texts)
                                   
1. castration, emasculation -- (neutering a male animal by removing the testicles)
2. castration -- (surgical removal of the testes or ovaries (usually to inhibit hormone secretion in cases of breast cancer in women or prostate cancer in men); "bilateral castration results in sterilization")
3. expurgation, castration -- (the deletion of objectionable parts from a literary work)
